Disgruntled Lawley residents took to the streets after their shacks were demolished by the Red Ants on instruction from the City of Johannesburg. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Disgruntled Lawley residents are protesting because their shacks were demolished by the Red Ants sent on instruction from the City of Johannesburg. Human Settlement Minister Lindiwe Sisulu says government wants to stop evictions and land invasions during the lockdown. Sisulu says Lawley residents should liaise with the Gauteng housing department to find a solution.